main event: A loud rotating sighting was reported in New Hampton, New Hampshire on September 9, 1955.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 15 minutes,The report included a radar tracking form,The report has been deemed inconclusive due to lack of information,The sighting is classified under case category D,The evaluator of the report was G.V. Jones.
witness description: No specific witness descriptions were provided in the report.
